[normal]sector 
[normal]size criteria 
[normal]is not a
[normal]n effective
[normal] way of tackling overcrowding given the geographical mismatch between households who are under-occupying and high levels of overcrowding
[normal]. It is also not a good way of making the best use of 
[normal]the 
[normal]affordable housing 
[normal]stock 
[normal]given the limited opportunities for people to move to smaller properties
[normal] within the sector. 
[normal]For example, a
[normal]nalysis from the Federation shows: 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]7.4
[normal]              
[normal]Recommendation: the Government should 
[normal]repeal
[normal] the social 
[normal]sector 
[normal]size criteria.  
